      <h1 class='title'>Freedom of Information</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 November 2003 vol 415 c37WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_37ws' title='Col. 37WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 November 2003 vol 415 c37WS' name='column_37ws' href='#column_37ws' rel='bookmark'>37WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0415P2_20031127_CWS_34'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-chris-leslie' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0415P2_20031127_CWS_34' title='Link to this speech by Mr Chris Leslie' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-chris-leslie" title="Mr Chris Leslie">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Constitutional Affairs (Mr. Christopher Leslie)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The Secretary of State for Constitutional Affairs has today laid before both Houses and published the Annual Report on bringing into force those provisions of the <a href="/acts/freedom-of-information-act-2000">Freedom of Information Act 2000</a> which are not yet fully in force. The Government is committed to bringing the <a href="/acts/freedom-of-information-act-2000">Freedom of Information Act</a> fully into force in January 2005. This report details what action has been taken as well as what arrangements are being made for the coming year. Copies of the report have been placed in the Library.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
